commit.message:
Bump version to 1.1.0

The rationale for increasing the minor version (instead of only the
patch level) is that we enforce a new version of the pulsectl dependency
with this update. With the new minor version we could (in theory) add
patch releases for 1.0.0, if someone needs to stick to the old pulsectl
version.

commit.message:
Add allow_suspend parameter to subscribe_peak_sample()

This allows to decide whether to use the DONT_INHIBIT_AUTO_SUSPEND flag
for the peak monitoring stream (useful for monitoring sinks; default in
pulsectl) or not (useful for monitoring sinks; current default behaviour
in pulsectl-async).
